import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    data.boxplot(column='precipitation', by='location', ax=ax)
    ax.set_xlabel('Location')
    ax.set_ylabel('Precipitation')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of precipitation across locations?')
    plt.suptitle('')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.plot(data['date'], data['temp_max'], label='Max Temperature')
    ax.plot(data['date'], data['temp_min'], label='Min Temperature')
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Temperature (°C)')
    ax.set_title('How does temperature vary over time?')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['wind'], data['temp_max'], alpha=0.5)
    plt.xlabel('Wind')
    plt.ylabel('Max Temperature')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between wind and temperature?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['weather'] = data['weather'].astype('category')
    data['location'] = data['location'].astype('category')
    data = data.groupby(['location', 'weather']).size().reset_index(name='counts')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.bar(data[data['location'] == 'Seattle']['weather'], data[data['location'] == 'Seattle']['counts'], color='blue', label='Seattle')
    ax.bar(data[data['location'] == 'New York']['weather'], data[data['location'] == 'New York']['counts'], color='orange', label='New York')
    ax.set_xlabel('Weather')
    ax.set_ylabel('Counts')
    ax.set_title('What is the most common type of weather in each location?')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
